50|$|SJRWMD {{is one of}} five water {{management}} districts that were established in 1972 by Chapter 373, Florida Statutes, as independent special districts and were empowered by the electorate in 1976 <b>to</b> <b>assess</b> ad valorem <b>taxes</b> <b>to</b> fund the management of the state’s water resources, and related land resources, to benefit people and the environment. Each {{water management}} district is administered by a Governing Board composed of residents appointed by the Governor and approved by the Florida Senate. All districts report directly to the governor.|$|R
